    "pages": [
      [
        "Page 1",
        "Long ago, a husband and wife lived beside a strange, high wall. Beyond the wall grew a garden full of leafy green rapunzel plants. And that garden belonged to a stern old witch."
      ],
      [
        "Page 2",
        "The wife peeked over the wall each day. \"I must taste those greens,\" she whispered. So her husband tiptoed over, snip-snip, and filled his basket. But the witch was watching."
      ],
      [
        "Page 3",
        "\"Thief!\" the witch cried, stepping from the shadows. The husband's heart thumped. \"Please, my wife is sick.\" The witch tilted her head. \"Take the greens. But your baby will belong to me.\""
      ],
      [
        "Page 4",
        "When a tiny baby girl was born, the witch came and carried her away. She named the child Rapunzel, after the leafy greens. And she raised her with strange, stern love."
      ],
      [
        "Page 5",
        "When Rapunzel turned twelve, the witch led her deep into the woods. There stood a tall, tall tower with no door and no stairs. Only one small window, high at the very top."
      ],
      [
        "Page 6",
        "Rapunzel's hair grew and grew, long and gold as sunshine. Every evening, the witch called up, \"Rapunzel, Rapunzel, let down your hair!\" And up she climbed, hand over hand."
      ],
      [
        "Page 7",
        "Rapunzel sang sweet songs from her window. Birds listened. Squirrels listened. One day a kind young prince rode by and listened too. \"Who sings so sweetly?\" he whispered, peering up."
      ],
      [
        "Page 8",
        "He hid and watched. He saw the witch call, \"Rapunzel, let down your hair!\" He saw the golden ladder tumble down. \"Aha!\" thought the prince. \"Now I know the secret.\""
      ],
      [
        "Page 9",
        "The next day he called softly, \"Rapunzel, Rapunzel, let down your hair!\" Up he climbed. Rapunzel gasped. But his eyes were gentle. Soon they were laughing like old friends."
      ],
      [
        "Page 10",
        "The prince visited again and again. They played games and shared stories. \"One day,\" he said, \"you could come away with me.\" Rapunzel smiled. She had never felt so happy."
      ],
      [
        "Page 11",
        "But Rapunzel forgot and said, \"Oh! Why are you so much heavier to pull up than the prince?\" The witch gasped. \"You wicked girl! You have tricked me!\" Her voice shook the tower."
      ],
      [
        "Page 12",
        "The witch took Rapunzel far away to a quiet meadow. Then she waited. When the prince called, she dropped the hair. Up he climbed — and found only the witch's angry stare."
      ],
      [
        "Page 13",
        "The prince wandered many months, searching. At last he heard singing in a meadow. Rapunzel! They hugged tight, tears shining. They rode home together and were married, happy forever after."
      ]
    ],
