    "description": "A clever cat with fine boots and a plan to make his master a king.",
    "duration": "5",
    "pages": [
      [
        "Page 1",
        "Once, a poor miller left his youngest son, Thomas, only one thing. A cat! Thomas sighed. \"A cat cannot fill my belly.\" But the cat grinned. \"Just wait,\" he purred. \"I have a plan.\""
      ],
      [
        "Page 2",
        "\"Bring me a sack,\" said the cat, \"and a fine pair of boots!\" Thomas laughed, but he found them. The cat pulled the boots on. Snap! Snap! Now he looked very grand indeed."
      ],
      [
        "Page 3",
        "Off trotted Puss to the meadow. He opened his sack and set it down like a trap. A plump rabbit hopped right in. \"Gotcha!\" whispered Puss, tying the sack with a clever little bow."
      ],
      [
        "Page 4",
        "Puss marched straight to the king's palace. He bowed low. \"A gift, Your Majesty, from my master, the Marquis of Carabas!\" The king smiled kindly. \"How generous!\" Puss winked. His plan had begun."
      ],
      [
        "Page 5",
        "Every week Puss brought rabbits and partridges. \"From the Marquis of Carabas!\" he always said. The king grew curious. \"This Marquis must be a fine fellow.\" Puss twirled his whiskers. Oh yes, indeed!"
      ],
      [
        "Page 6",
        "One sunny day, Puss heard the king's carriage was coming. He raced to Thomas. \"Quick! Jump in the river and splash!\" Thomas blinked. \"Trust me,\" purred Puss. Splash, splash, into the water he went."
      ],
      [
        "Page 7",
        "\"Help! Thieves took my master's clothes!\" Puss cried as the carriage rolled by. The king stopped at once. He gave Thomas fine velvet robes. A princess peeked out and smiled. Thomas smiled back shyly."
      ],
      [
        "Page 8",
        "The carriage rolled on. Puss ran ahead through the fields. He met farmers working. \"When the king asks, say this land belongs to the Marquis of Carabas! Otherwise, hop like bunnies!\" The farmers nodded quickly."
      ],
      [
        "Page 9",
        "\"Whose fields are these?\" asked the king. \"The Marquis of Carabas, sire!\" sang the farmers. On and on rolled the carriage, past wheat and orchards and meadows. The king's eyes grew wider and wider."
      ],
      [
        "Page 10",
        "Now Puss scampered up to a great stone castle. Inside lived a grumpy ogre with stompy boots. \"I hear you can turn into anything,\" Puss said, bowing. The ogre grinned. \"Watch this!\" POOF! A lion!"
      ],
      [
        "Page 11",
        "Puss clapped politely. \"Amazing! But could you turn into something tiny, like a mouse?\" The ogre huffed. \"Easy!\" POOF! A little grey mouse scampered across the floor. Puss pounced and scooped him into a teacup."
      ],
      [
        "Page 12",
        "\"Welcome to my master's castle!\" Puss purred as the carriage arrived. Thomas gasped. The king cheered. A grand feast was waiting. The little mouse, safely in his teacup, was sent off to a cozy meadow."
      ],
      [
        "Page 13",
        "The king hugged Thomas. The princess took his hand, and soon they were married. Thomas became a true Marquis at last! And clever Puss? He sat on a velvet cushion, purring happily ever after."
      ]
    ],
