    "id": "classic_snow_queen",
    "title": "The Snow Queen",
    "emoji": "❄️",
    "color": "#6b90b5",
    "genre": "classics",
    "age": "4-7",
    "isClassic": true,
    "originalAuthor": "Hans Christian Andersen",
    "description": "A brave girl travels far to save her dearest friend.",
    "duration": "5",
    "pages": [
      [
        "Page 1",
        "In a little town of red rooftops lived two best friends, Gerda and Kai. They grew roses together in a window box. They laughed together. They shared every single secret. They were as close as two friends could be."
      ],
      [
        "Page 2",
        "One winter day, something changed in Kai. His smile turned chilly. \"Your roses look silly,\" he said. Gerda blinked, surprised. Kai grabbed his sled and ran off into the swirling snow without even saying goodbye."
      ],
      [
        "Page 3",
        "High above, a sparkling sleigh glided down. Inside sat the Snow Queen, tall and pale, wrapped in silver furs. \"Come with me, little one,\" she whispered. She wrapped Kai in her cloak and whisked him far, far away."
      ],
      [
        "Page 4",
        "Morning came, but Kai did not. Gerda waited and waited by the window. Her heart thumped. \"I will find him,\" she said bravely. She pulled on her red boots and stepped out into the wide, snowy world."
      ],
      [
        "Page 5",
        "Gerda walked until she met a river. \"River, have you seen Kai?\" The river only gurgled and shone. So Gerda climbed into a little boat and let the water carry her gently onward, past reeds and sleeping swans."
      ],
      [
        "Page 6",
        "The boat bumped into a flowery garden. A kind old woman with a sunhat smiled. \"Stay, child, and rest.\" But the roses whispered, \"Your friend is not here.\" So Gerda hugged the woman and hurried on."
      ],
      [
        "Page 7",
        "A clever crow hopped beside her. \"Caw! I know a prince who might be Kai!\" He led Gerda to a grand palace. But the prince had brown curls, not Kai's. The prince was kind. He gave her warm mittens and a golden coach."
      ],
      [
        "Page 8",
        "Through the forest rolled the coach. Suddenly — thump! — robbers leapt out! A little robber girl with wild hair peeked inside. \"Oh, you are sweet,\" she grinned. \"You shall be my friend tonight, but I won't hurt you.\"\""
      ],
      [
        "Page 9",
        "In the robber den, a reindeer whispered, \"I know where the Snow Queen lives.\" The little robber girl's eyes grew soft. \"Then go,\" she said. \"Take my reindeer. Find your Kai.\" She wrapped Gerda in furs and kissed her cheek."
      ],
      [
        "Page 10",
        "North they galloped, over frozen rivers and silver hills. The reindeer's hooves drummed on the ice. Stars shimmered like scattered sugar. Gerda held tight, her breath puffing in little clouds. \"Almost there, almost there,\" she whispered."
      ],
      [
        "Page 11",
        "At last — a palace of glittering ice! Inside sat Kai, still and pale, stacking frozen puzzle pieces. \"Kai! It's me!\" Gerda cried. But Kai only stared, cold as winter, as if he could not hear her at all."
      ],
      [
        "Page 12",
        "Gerda wrapped her arms around him. Her warm tears fell onto his cheek. Slowly, slowly, Kai's eyes softened. He blinked. He smiled. \"Gerda? My Gerda!\" The icy palace shivered. Love had thawed his frozen heart clean through."
      ],
      [
        "Page 13",
        "Hand in hand, they rode the reindeer home. The roses were blooming again in the window box. Summer sunshine warmed the rooftops. Gerda and Kai laughed and shared secrets, best friends forever — and never, ever apart again."
      ]
    ],
